Nothing to apologize for at all! You uploaded this and for that I'm grateful!

I don't need the journal, I'm using my heart rate monitor and a calorie counter already so it's not a big deal. I was just commenting on it for other people looking at it. Other than one page being out of order for the scans of the books, the pdfs are perfect.

In the world of where people are used to 1080p and 720p, the video's resolution is 640x480. I rated it on what other people might think about it. Again, like the hand outs, this doesn't bother me at all but it isn't perfect. If that is the quality of the videos then that's unimpressive and I'm surprised people actually pay that much for the videos. This (http://i1026.photobucket.com/albums/y322/andyoubrute/1.png) is what it looked like for me. At that quality it sort of irked me as I'm enjoy giffing/making graphics with CS5. I can't see myself doing much with this - the 30DS gif set I created a while back was super popular. It doesn't destroy the view but it's not pretty. It's definitely work-able and passes. When you're working out a few metres away it's going to be a lot more clear.

I wasn't rating the video on the content. That I'm sure is great, as why I downloaded it. [Although I can't say for sure as I haven't actually completed it.] I loved the 30 Day Shred, had great results [-10lbs, -3 inches off my waist] and am eager to start this. However like you said about the meal plan, it's not in my budget to buy the actual program XD I'm a poor student! I couldn't even afford to download this on my internet plan, I did it at my university. 

(By the way, I loved the speed of downloading this. Compared to the original on one here it was very fast - took less than 4 hours and I seeded about 9 gigs of it before I had to leave school.)
